This page is functional, but is missing some feature parity from the guidebook. Namely, some recipe types, such as grinding and microwaving, are missing. This is most evident in the Nourishment section. Please, bear the missing features in mind, as they may misrepresent chemicals in their current state.
"Chemistry" redirects here. For the job, see Chemist.

Reagents are all substances in Space Station 14, including elements, gases, drinks, drugs, and other chemicals. This page is a reference page for all reagents in the game.

    Epinephrine

    Recipe

    Epinephrine
    Phenol [1]
    Acetone [1]
    Chlorine [1]
    Hydroxide [1]
    Mix
    Epinephrine [4]

    Effects

    Medicine (0.5u per second)
    • Removes 5u of histamine from the solution when there's at least 45u of histamine
    • Heals 0.5 brute (0.2 blunt, 0.2 slash and 0.2 piercing), 0.5 burn (0.1 heat, 0.1 shock, 0.1 cold and 0.1 caustic), 3 asphyxiation, and 0.5 poison when the mob is critical and there's at most 20u of epinephrine
    • Deals 1 asphyxiation and 1 poison when there's at least 20u of epinephrine
    • Removes 2u of heartbreaker toxin from the solution
    • Removes 1u of epinephrine from the solution when there's at least 1u of heartbreaker toxin
    • Has a 10% chance to add 4u of histamine to the solution when there's at least 1u of heartbreaker toxin
    • Removes 0.75s of stun
    • Removes 0.75s of knockdown
    • Causes adrenaline for at least 5s without accumulation

    An effective stabilizing chemical used to keep a critical person from dying to asphyxiation while patching up minor damage during crit.     Chemical Matter Reactions

    Soap

    15u Fat, 10u Table Salt, and 10u Water creates 1 bar of soap.

    15u Fat, 10u Table Salt, and 10u Blood creates 1 bar of homemade soap.

    Meatification

    25u Fat, 5u Nutriment, 10u Blood, and 10u Carbon creates 1 slab of meat.

    Plastic Sheets

    5u Oil, 3u Ash, and 2u Sulfuric Acid creates 1 sheet of plastic (heat to 378K)

    Flash Freeze

    1u of Fresium and 1u of Water creates 1 mole of Frezon and 5u of ice.

    Colored Crystal Shards

    15u Sugar, 15u Water, and 5u Ethanol creates one randomly colored crystal shard.

    Gunpowder

    6u Potassium, 2u Sulfur, and 2u Charcoal will create 1 piece of gunpowder.

    Chemical Effect Reactions

    Explosive

    Equal parts Potassium + Water explodes when mixed.

    The reaction to create Chlorine Trifluoride causes an explosion.

    Equal parts Juice that makes you Weh + Juice that makes you Hew explodes when mixed.

    Smoke

    Equal parts Phosphorus + Potassium + Sugar

    When mixed, causes any additional chemical within the solution to spread as smoke. Blocks the line of sight of observers, and anyone without internals can ingest it. Increasing the amount of reagents will create more smoke.

    Foam

    Equal parts Water + Fluorosurfactant

    When mixed, causes any additional chemical within the solution to spread as a foam. Slips anyone who runs in it, and anyone without internals can ingest it. Increasing the amount of reagents will create more foam. Space Cleaner foam will convert any spilled liquid it touches into water, while Space Lube and Space Glue foam will leave respective puddles on the floor.

    Metal Foam

    3 parts Aluminum or Iron, 1 part Foaming Agent, 1 part Fluorosulfuric acid

    When mixed, causes any iron or aluminum in the solution to foam into a solid wall. Increasing the amount of reagents will create more foam.

    Flash

    Equal parts Aluminum + Potassium + Sulfur

    When mixed, creates a flash that interferes with the vision of those nearby.

    EMP

    Equal parts Iron + Uranium + Aluminum

    When mixed, causes an EMP explosion that drains the energy of nearby objects for 15 seconds. Increasing the amount of reagent increases the range of the explosion, up to 6 tiles when using 30 units of each reagent.

    Plasma Gas

    The reaction to create Phlogiston creates plasma gas as a by-product.
